history.text: Have you seen Zootopia?  It is a good kids movie.
Yes I have. Would you watch it again?
Probably if someone wanted to watch it.
It has the anthropomorphic mammals.
Me too. Do you like Jason Bateman? I think he was a good choice to voie a character.
*voice
Yes Jason Bateman was the fox.
He's very funny.
Yes he is, that is true.
It has state of the art animation too.
Did you find the animations to be cute? I thought they were adorable!
Yes I thought it was "visually stunning" with the city scapes and whatnot.
And yes the character animation was very good as well.
I agree. Rotten Tomatoes even gave it a score of 8/10 which is higher than many movies
Yes that is true, it is highly rated.
It also has a good message to it- Especially how we should look past stereotypes.
Definitely.  one should avoid species-ism.
Do you like how the main character is a rabbit or would you prefer a different animal?
No the rabbit was fine.  The plot involved predators going savage and the rabbit said the wrong thing at the press conference and made the fox upset.
Yes. However the fox was a criminal. I'm glad Judy got praised for solving the case.
Her words caused a lot of tension between predators and prey throughout the city.  It was unintentional though.
That problem causes her to quit her job. What a shame
That was too bad, she wasn't the best at handling the media like a politician.
It is also natural for there to be tension between predators and prey though.
Yes but you have to handle that too, just like different kinds of humans in the real world.  The savagery of the predators was caused by "night howlers" which were a flower.
Which were a type of flower/
It's comparable to the real world where drugs alter people's behavior and cause problems.
Yes, but Bellwether the deputy mayor was having predators shot with a serum from the flowers in order to destabilize everything and become Mayor.
That's wrong on many levels. Judy should have been the mayor because you could see that she had good intentions.

Nah, Judy wasn't enough of a politician.  The lion was a decent mayor, but Bellwether tried to undermine the credibility of all predators in order to take control and make predators second class citizens, sort of a reverse-racist thing because in nature predators are at the top of the food chain.
Well we've both had at least 12 entries so far, but the finish conversation button is grayed out.
That's another way of seeing it. Except if Judy were mayor instead she may have been less experienced but less bad things would have happened.
I guess so, maybe the sheep deputy mayor wouldn't have been as mad because Judy would have been nicer to her.
